Central NJ Cyclocross Clinic
description:
Rutgers University-Raleigh Cycling Team is proud to present a cyclocross skills clinic at the Livingston Campus of Rutgers University in Piscataway, NJ. 

Whether you\'ve heard about cyclocross and wanted to give it a try, or you\'ve done a few races and want to learn the techniques, or you\'re an experienced racer looking to further polish your skills, this clinic will provide a great head start to your 2010 cyclocross season.
course:
Topics Covered:
		Safety
		Equipment, bike fit, wheel/tire selection, tire pressure
		Race start technique
		First lab tips
		Cornering & proper breaking
		Dismounting
		Portaging/Shouldering
		Remounting
		Training Theory
		Race Day Prep
		Race Ethics
		Off Camber Riding 
		Bike Changes
		Last Lap tactics		

8PM BBQ for all participants
registration:
For USAC/riders not currently on a NCCA-recognized collegiate teams, the fee is $25/day. A valid USAC license is required; one-day licenses will be available for an additional $5. 

For collegiate riders, the fee is $12.5/day. A valid NCCA license is required; one-day licenses will be available for an additional $5. 

NO REFUNDS FOR ANY REASON - NO DAY OF REGISTRATION

Participant Check In will begin a 4:00 PM on Saturday Aug 6th and 9:00AM on Sunday Aug 7th. The Clinic will begin at 5:00 PM on Aug 6th, and 10:00 on August 7th.
notes:
Categories: 

Beginner: You have 0-2 years of cyclocross racing experience. You may know the basics of the sport, but you are looking for step-by-step guidance in cyclocross technique and equipment set up.

Advanced: You have 2+ years of cyclocross racing experience, or you\'ve been to a clinic before and want to brush up on the basics before polishing your skills further and learning some advanced technique.
